A senior Soviet official said a visit toMoscow by U.S. Secretary of State George Shultz for armsdiscussions was under consideration.    Deputy Foreign Minister Alexander Bessmertnykh told a newsconference such a visit would be part of continuing contactsbetween the two powers "in the framework of security questions."    Earlier, U.S. Officials with Shultz in Peking said he waslikely to go to Moscow soon following Kremlin leader MikhailGorbachev's weekend proposal for a separate agreement onwithdrawing Soviet and American medium-range missiles fromEurope.&#3;